SUMMARY:Collective Views: A Symposium on Photography and Toronto
DESCRIPTION:Join MOCA Toronto and the AGO for a symposium that offers a chance to reflect on Toronto and its relationship to photography. Across sessions spanning the 1970s to the present\, it brings together artists\, artworks\, cultural figures\, scholars\, exhibitions\, organizations\, collections\, art schools\, and publications that have shaped evolving understandings of the city and the medium—revealing Toronto as a place where photography continues to be vital\, generative\, and connective. \nThe symposium is co-presented on the occasion of Collective Visions: Celebrating 25 Years of Photography at the AGO and Jeff Wall Photographs 1984–2023 at MOCA. \nVisit our website for the full schedule and pricing. \nImage Credit: June Clark. Henrys on Church Street\, 1974 (printed 2023). Gelatin silver print\, Overall: 21 x 30.5 cm. Art Gallery of Ontario. Purchase\, 2023. © June Clark. Photo: AGO. 2023/103.
URL:https://nowtoronto.com/event/collective-views-a-symposium-on-photography-and-toronto/
LOCATION:Museum of Contemporary Art Toronto Canada\, 158 Sterling Rd #100\, Toronto\, ON M6R 2B7\, Canada\, Old Toronto\, Toronto\, Ontario\, M6R 2B7
CATEGORIES:Art & Design,Talks & Panels
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://nowtoronto.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/collective-views-a-symposium-on-photography-and-toronto.jpg
END:VEVENT
