SUMMARY:A Mirrror
DESCRIPTION:Actors Repertory Company (ARC) presents the Toronto premiere of A Mirror by award-winning British playwright Sam Holcroft\, running for a limited time from March 10 to 28\, 2026 at 918 Bathurst Centre for Culture\, Arts\, Media & Education\, Toronto. \nGet ready for the wedding of the year! It is with great pleasure that Leyla and Joel invite you to celebrate their marriage this March. Dress code is informal. Doors open at 7:30 p.m.\, followed by the exchange of vows. And at our signal\, the entertainment begins. \nIt will be performed in Toronto by Rita Dottor (Natasha\, Pierre & the Great Comet of 1812)\, Jonelle Gunderson (To Kill a Mockingbird\, The Ideal Husband)\, Craig Lauzon (The Welkin\, Bad Roads)\, Paul Smith  (Dead Korean Girl Comedy Show)\, Courtenay Stevens (La Bête\, The Boys)\, and Nabil Traboulsi  (Martyr\, Rockabye).
URL:https://nowtoronto.com/event/a-mirrror/
LOCATION:918 Bathurst Centre for Culture\, 918 Bathurst St\, Toronto\, ON M5R 3G5\, Canada\, Old Toronto\, Toronto\, Ontario\, M5R 3G5
CATEGORIES:Theatre & Opera
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://nowtoronto.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/a-mirrror.png
END:VEVENT
